WES MOORE, Governor Ch. 5
Chapter 5
(Senate Bill 283)
AN ACT concerning
Creation of a State Debt – Maryland Consolidated Capital Bond Loan of 2026,
and the Maryland Consolidated Capital Bond Loans of 2005, 2014, 2015, 2016,
2017, 2018, 2019, 2020, 2021, 2022, 2023, 2024, and 2025
FOR the purpose of authorizing the creation of a State Debt in the amount of One Billion,
Eight Hundred and Twenty–Four Million, Seven Hundred and Eighty–Two
Thousand Dollars ($1,824,782,000) One Billion, Seven Hundred and Fifty–Eight
Million, Two Hundred and Sixty–One Thousand, Nine Hundred and Six Dollars
($1,758,261,906) One Billion, Eight Hundred and Thirty–Nine Million, Nine
Hundred and Forty Thousand, Four Hundred and Six Dollars ($1,839,940,406) One
Billion, Eight Hundred and Forty–Seven Million, and Ninety–Nine Thousand
Dollars ($1,847,099,000), the proceeds to be used for certain necessary building,
construction, demolition, planning, renovation, conversion, replacement, and capital
equipment purchases of the State, for acquiring certain real estate in connection
therewith, and for grants to certain subdivisions and other organizations for certain
development and improvement purposes; subject to certain requirements that
certain matching funds be provided and expended by certain dates; providing
generally for the issuance and sale of bonds evidencing the loan; imposing a certain
tax on all assessable property in the State; specifying the use of certain school
construction funds; removing certain matching fund requirements; requiring that
certain grantees convey certain easements under certain circumstances to the
Maryland Historical Trust; providing that the proceeds of certain loans must be
expended or encumbered by a certain date; repealing requirements for certain
grantees to present evidence to the Board of Public Works that certain matching funds
will be provided on or before a certain date; providing that certain funds may be used
only for certain purposes; requiring the Department of General Services to record
certain correct information in certain grant agreements under certain
circumstances, notwithstanding certain differences; authorizing the Board of Public
Works, under certain circumstances, to approve certain appropriations,
notwithstanding certain differences; altering and clarifying certain provisions of law
relating to capital expenditures and grants for capital projects; repealing the
termination of authority to spend an appropriation for a capital project if certain
conditions are not met within a certain 2–year period, and making the repeal
applicable retroactively; exempting money authorized for certain programs from the
requirement that an authorization of State debt terminates 7 years after the date of
authorization, and making the exemption applicable retroactively; requiring certain
parking spaces allocated for employees of the General Assembly in a certain parking
facility to be allocated in a certain manner during a certain period of time each year;
authorizing certain unexpended appropriations in certain prior capital budgets and
bond loans to be expended for other public projects; altering certain requirements for
certain programs in certain prior capital budgets and bond loans; reducing prior
– 1 –

Ch. 5 2026 LAWS OF MARYLAND
authorizations of State Debt; requiring that certain projects be constructed at certain
locations; adding, altering, and repealing certain requirements for certain
appropriations; altering and expanding the authorized purpose of certain grants;
providing that certain grants may not terminate before certain dates; authorizing
premiums from the sale of State bonds in certain fiscal years to be used for certain
purposes; requiring the Comptroller to make certain transfers, adjustments, and
reconciliations; repealing certain Maryland Consolidated Capital Bond Loan
Preauthorization acts; specifying the use of certain project funds; authorizing the
creation of State Debt in certain years to be used for certain purposes; clarifying the
use of certain bond proceeds; and generally relating to the financing of certain capital
projects.
